The paper focuses on identifying and characterizing bots that automate developer activity in OSS projects, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The use of automation tools and the analysis of their activity patterns also relates to topics in social computing (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper uses machine learning techniques to detect bots, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper analyzes the types of files modified by bots, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
